  <Section
    id="invariants"
    label="§01 · Invariants"
    title="Invariants that must be protected"
    lede="Exam list: retellability beats a green checklist."
  >
    <ol class="plain-list numbered invariants">
      <li>Log is source of truth; state is a materialized view.</li>
      <li>UI transcript is never canonical for completed semantics.</li>
      <li>Exactly one valid terminal RuntimeEvent per terminated Invocation/Run.</li>
      <li>Terminal header commit requires a durable terminal fact (or an explicit repair path).</li>
      <li>Late events cannot override an accepted terminal.</li>
      <li>Permission/usage/artifact travel as actions, not chat masquerade.</li>
      <li>Tool call/result pairing remains reconstructible.</li>
      <li>Partial stream facts are replaceable; durable facts are not silent deltas forever.</li>
      <li>Recovery repairs projections from durable facts; it does not invent success; unknown tool combinations fail closed.</li>
      <li>Sandbox selection does not grant approval; required-but-missing backend fails closed — never silent host.</li>
      <li>Request materialization may evolve; message facts stay stable (this cost spine).</li>
    </ol>
    <p>
      Intellectual lineage (coarse): ADK-style “Session history is fact, working context is
      projection,” plus log-first / event-sourcing intuition from distributed systems — never treat
      every downstream view as an independent truth. §02 builds Tool Result evidence layers; §03
      keeps Compaction as projection-only; §04 wraps cross-Attempt TaskRun envelopes and distinguishes
      them from the session task ledger.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section
    id="asides"
    label="§01 · Asides"
    title="History aside index"
    lede="Mechanism PRs first; docs-land secondary."
  >
